{{Sunni Islam|Sunni Schools of Law}}
The '''Laythi''' ({{lang-ar|الليث}}) [[madhhab]] was an 8th-century religious law school of [[Fiqh]] within [[Sunni Islam]] whose Imam was [[Al-Layth ibn Sa'd]].

